{
  "name": "Heavenly Foot of Pain",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Taijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You put an enormous amount of chakra into the heel of your foot as you make a single downward kick. Make a Taijutsu attack against a target in range. On a hit target takes 7d10 Bludgeoning damage.</p><p>If this jutsu is used as a Finisher, additionally, all surrounding creatures, objects and structures (excluding you), within 30 feet of the target must succeed a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save they fall prone, are knocked into the air 30 feet, suffering falling damage and are incapacitated until the end of the current turn.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above B-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 1d10.</p>",
